# CODEOWNERS — SPIRAL Repository
#
# Rules apply in last-match-wins order. The most specific patterns should
# appear last so they override broader rules.
#
# Workflow files and security configuration require explicit approval from
# a designated security reviewer before merge. This ensures that supply-chain
# attacks (e.g., injected malicious actions or secret-exfiltration steps)
# are caught by a human before they reach the main branch.
#
# See CONTRIBUTING.md for the rationale and the SHA-pin update process.

# Default owners for everything in the repository
* @spiral-team

# GitHub Actions workflows — require security review on every change.
# Rationale: mutable action tags can be silently replaced with malicious code;
# SHA pins must be verified by a reviewer who understands supply-chain risks.
.github/workflows/ @spiral-security-team

# Security-sensitive configuration files — same reviewer requirement
.github/CODEOWNERS @spiral-security-team
.github/SECURITY.md @spiral-security-team
.github/dependabot.yml @spiral-security-team
